Jeep XJ Intelligent Fan Controller
Overview
This project solves a critical overheating issue on a 2001 Jeep Cherokee XJ during stop-and-go traffic. The issue is caused by the factory design, where the automatic transmission fluid (ATF) cooler sits on the cold side of the radiator, pre-heating coolant before it reaches the engine.

To address this, I designed a custom fan controller using a Beetle CM-32U4 microcontroller, a DS18B20 temperature sensor, and discrete NPN transistors to control a 3-fan shroud setup. The controller activates fans based on temperature thresholds to keep the engine operating around 210Â°F, even during slow driving.

